race.comment: Good contest to see us out. BRIMARVI ROSEMARIE (9) finally broke through last time when knocking off a perennial placegetter in town nine days ago. Full of confidence now and can keep the ball rolling. SIR RANDOLPH (3) comes through some  solid form races and drops back to a winning trip, with Pannell sticking. Ready to win. ANDREW'S MEMORY (6) has just been struggling to put it all together but backs up quickly here and doesn't have to improve much to strike through.  CHARLESFORT (7) hasn't had much luck this prep and will likely have to weave another late passage from his draw. Watch for him launching. COME ALONG JEFFREY (1) is knocking on the door and is worth keeping safe on best figures.
